{
  "texts": [
    "U-Net is an improved version that can concatenate the features in all resolution layers, allowing it to focus on even more detailed objects than the FCN models.",
    "The training dataset for the neural network models was prepared using data expansion from training images.",
    "First, for a pair of original secondary electron images of a certain z-section obtained by the 3D imaging mentioned above and its manually segmented image, a training dataset of 1000 images was created by cutting them from random positions to 256 × 256- pixel size and adding rotation and flipping operations randomly.",
    "Next, a test dataset of 1000 images for evaluating the accuracy of the classical thresholding method and neural network models were created using data expansion in the same way: for a pair of original secondary electron images of 1100 × 924-pixel size and their manually segmented image, a 256 × 256pixel size cropping was performed from random positions, and rotation and flipping operations were also applied.",
    "Consequently, 10 training datasets and 10 test datasets were created."
  ]
}